<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="H" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Hurt2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Hurt,</orth> vb. (impf. and part. <emph>hurt</emph>) 1) to harm, to injure, to pain, to do mischief, to vex; absol.: <cit><quote>have power to h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 94.1" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 94, 1</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>give delight and h. not,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 3.2.145" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. III, 2, 145</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 3.3.66" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 66</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 5.1.190" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado V, 1, 190</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 5.2.14" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 14</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 3.3.53" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A III, 3, 53</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.6.94" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C II, 6, 94</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 5.3.20" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. V, 3, 20</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 2.2.77" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. II, 2, 77</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 4.7.124" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. IV, 7, 124</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 5.2.299" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. V, 2, 299</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 1.6.95" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. I, 6, 95</bibl>. With an accus.: <cit><quote>this nor --s him nor profits you,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 4.3.128" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. IV, 3, 128</bibl></cit>. <emph>it</emph> (wit) <cit><quote>--s nobody,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 5.1.165" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado V, 1, 165</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. ado 5.2.16" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 16</bibl>. <cit><quote>it --s not him that he is loved of me,</quote> <bibl n="shak. aww 1.3.202" default="NO" valid="yes">Alls I, 3, 202</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. jn 4.3.33" default="NO" valid="yes">John IV, 3, 33</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 4.6.20" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C IV, 6, 20</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 4.6.20" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C IV, 6, 20</bibl> <bibl n="shak. h8 3.1.160" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 III, 1, 160</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 4.6.25" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. IV, 6, 25</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 2.3.204" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 3, 204</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 3.1.92" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 92</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 3.4.25" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. III, 4, 25</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 4.1.18" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 18</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 2.5.81" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. II, 5, 81</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 1.2.35" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. I, 2, 35</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 1.1.100" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. I, 1, 100</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 4.1.78" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 78</bibl>.<lb />2) to do bodily harm, to pain, to strike, to wound; tr.: <cit><quote>you h. my hand with wringing,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 421" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 421</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>h. him not,</quote> <bibl n="shak. err 5.33" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. V, 33</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>poor h. fowl,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 2.1.209" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado II, 1, 209</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>how they might h. their enemies,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 5.1.98" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 98</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.269" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. III, 2, 269</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.269" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. III, 2, 269</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mv 3.1.63" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. III, 1, 63</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.5.25" default="NO" valid="yes">As III, 5, 25</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 3.5.90" default="NO" valid="yes">Alls III, 5, 90</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 3.2.37" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. III, 2, 37</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 3.4.330" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 4, 330</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 3.4.330" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 4, 330</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tn 5.190.330" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 190</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 5.190.330" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 190</bibl> <bibl n="sh